<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.44.12-13_0001" />

<fw type="curatorial">12</fw>

<fw type="letterhead">
<hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>
<lb/>
<hi rend="caps">ROUTE 7 SKYRIM FARM</hi>
<lb/>
<hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</hi>  
</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>Nov. 8, 64</dateline>


<salute>Dear Friend:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Hurrah for Wilcox! I'm glad I knew him. What a life he had here! And, better still, what a life he has just begun!</p>

<p>I'm excited about the trip you are planning! <hi rend="double underline">What</hi> a trip! And how 
<hi rend="underline">right</hi> it is that you and Nita can <hi rend="underline">make</hi> it together! So often good things happen when there's no one to share.</p>

<p>It's dear of you &#8212; and <hi rend="underline">quite</hi> like you &#8212; to care about preserving my voice on records. Sandy Gray has a number of tapes all ready for processing, and 
   
   <note type="authorial">(over)</note>

<pb facs="nei.44.12-13_0002"/>
<fw type="curatorial">13</fw>

sooner or later these will be used to make discs.</p>

<p>Yesterday there was a nice little ceremony in the Library here when the <hi rend="caps">TV</hi> station presented five of my half-hour videotapes and kinoscopes to the Western <hi rend="caps">MSS</hi> Collection &#8212; all to be a part of the Neihardt Memorial Collection <del><unclear>(Librar</unclear></del>(my Library, letters, <hi rend="caps">MSS</hi>, papers etc). My 
<hi rend="underline">bronze bust</hi> will guard the entrance to this collection. Isn't this too good almost to believe?!</p>

<p>You are going to have the <hi rend="double underline">time of your lives</hi> together, and I'm 
<hi rend="underline">so</hi> happy about it</p>
<closer>
<salute>Affectionately</salute> <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
</closer>


</div1>
